7,"age":45,"year":"1455","julianDay":2252488,"title":"Wars of the Roses","description":"Wars of the Roses was a series of English civil wars for control of the throne of England between the royal families House of Lancaster and the House of York. The name of the war was derived as the red rose was the symbol of the Lancastrians and the white rose was the symbol of the Yorks.","url":"https://www.history.com/topics/british-history/wars-of-the-roses","urlTitle":"History - Wars of the Roses","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"When Anne Humberton was born in 1410, in Walkern, Hertfordshire, England, her father, Edward Humberton, was 20 and her mother, Mrs. Edward Humberton, was 20. She married Thomas James Castell about 1430. They were the parents of at least 1 son. She died in East Hatley, Cambridgeshire, England."},"et":{"1410–":"1410–Surnud","1410–Female":"1410–Surnud","1410–1459":"1410–1459","1430–1504":"1430–1504","1390–1470":"1390–1470","1390–Female":"1390–Surnud","1459":"1459","1455":"1455","1410":"1410","Abt 1430":"umbes 1430","1430":"1430","1470":"1470","about 1430":"umbes 1430","1390":"1390","1504":"1504","Walkern, Hertfordshire, England":"Walkern, Hertfordshire, England","East Hatley, South Cambridgeshire district, Cambridgeshire, England, United Kingdom":"East Hatley, Cambridgeshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","East Hatley, Cambridgeshire, England":"East Hatley, Cambridgeshire, England"},"fi":{"1410–":"1410–Kuollut","1410–Female":"1410–Kuollut","1410–1459":"1410–1459","1430–1504":"1430–1504","1390–1470":"1390–1470","1390–Female":"1390–Kuollut","1459":"1459","1455":"1455","1410":"1410","Abt 1430":"noin 1430","1430":"1430","1470":"1470","about 1430":"noin 1430","1390":"1390","1504":"1504","Walkern, Hertfordshire, England":"Walkern, Hertfordshire, England","East Hatley, South Cambridgeshire district, Cambridgeshire, England, United Kingdom":"East Hatley, Cambridgeshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","East Hatley, Cambridgeshire, England":"East Hatley, 